{:metadata {:description [{"text" "<p>This entry represents the TonB-dependent outer membrane haem/haemoglobin receptor/transporter found in bacteria which live in contact with animals (which contain haemoglobin or other haem-bearing globins) or legumes (which contain leghaemoglobin). Some species such as Nostoc, Caulobacter and Chlorobium do not have an obvious source of haemoglobin-like proteins in their biological niche and so the possibility exists that they act on some other substance.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The haem transport system from haem-haemopexin from Haemophilus influenzae consists of HxuC, a haem receptor, and the two-partner-secretion system HxuB/HxuA. HxuB and HxuA are required only for utilization of haem from haem-haemopexin complexe. HxuA forms complexes with haem-haemopexin, leading to haem release and its capture by TonB-dependent receptor HxuC. HxuC likely functions as an outer-membrane haem-binding protein and/or transmembrane transport protein [[cite:PUB00087373], [cite:PUB00087378]].</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false}], :is-reviewed-llm false, :representative-structure nil, :overlaps-with [{"accession" "IPR036942", "name" "TonB-dependent receptor-like, beta-barrel domain superfamily", "type" "homologous_superfamily"}], :member-databases {"ncbifam" {"TIGR01785" "TonB-dependent heme/hemoglobin receptor family protein"}}, :is-updated-llm false, :name {"name" "TonB-dependent haem/haemoglobin receptor", "short" "TonB_haem/Hb_rcpt"}, :wikipedia nil, :source-database "interpro", :type "family", :counters {"structures" 6, "domain_architectures" 0, "proteomes" 1205, "taxa" 6105, "subfamilies" 0, "interactions" 0, "matches" 7639, "sets" 0, "proteins" 7639, "structural_models" {"alphafold" 5864}, "pathways" 0}, :integrated nil, :cross-references {}, :set-info nil, :accession "IPR011276", :literature {"PUB00087373" {"URL" nil, "issue" nil, "authors" ["Zambolin S" "Clantin B" "Chami M" "Hoos S" "Haouz A" "Villeret V" "Delepelaire P."], "ISO_jou